The paper deals with cryptanalysis of two variants of the McEliece cryptosystem, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The variants are based on quasi-cyclic codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the complexity of the attacks, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a structural attack, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SI).
